@NODE "AUTH" "About the Author"
@NEXT "CREDS"
@PREV "PICMENÜ"
@TOC "MAIN"
@Font Helvetica.font 13
@{jcenter}


I am 27 jears old, live in Austria near the german border
and use the Amiga for quite some time now. My main interests
are in graphics and games.
After watching some of Eric Schwartze´s Animations and
Pictures, I wanted to do something like that myselfe, so I
searched different Books for an Animal to antropomorphise.
This turned out to be more difficult than expected, because
almost every cute little mammal I found was either already
used in some cartoons or at least showed so many simmilarities
in appearence to existing characters, that I decided to avoid
it in order not to come out with some sort of a clone. After
a full month of searching I stumbled about a picture of a
Garden Dormouse and instantly decided that this was almost
ideal. After painting 6 pictures of @{"Dominique" Link "DOMINFO"} I finally
found the guts to introduce my work to the public and up=
loaded my first file to the Aminet. Since then i´m producing
about 2 pictures a month and uploading them about every 2
month´s to the Aminet.

If anybody wants to contact me, please write, since I don´t
have direct access to the Aminet or any Mailbox.
Adress:

