Greetings to all of you, Amiga Brothers and Sisters and especially the furry
fans amongst you. Once again I´m uploading 2 new pictures with Dominique.
Both of this Pictures are painted completely by hand in 256 colors and occupy
more than 640x512 pixels so some picture displayers which don´t read the
screen resolution chunks may open strange unintended screenmodes cropping
away the pictures edges or changing the pixle ratio by doing so. If this
happens, I suggest you use Multiview which doesn´t experience this problems.
This Amigaguide-Document makes use of the Helvetica.font size 13 which under
normal circumstances should be in your fonts drawer. This font doesn´t use
a fixed width, so if you for some reasons deleted it and Amigaguide uses the
standard Topaz-Font, some Pages may look pretty strange.

@ENDNODE

